\"state\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even taking into account the North's reluctance to portray South Korea in a positive light, the blackout is a bit mysterious.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1041, \"end\": 1052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.346934963160536e-16, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"account\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1006}, {\"ngram\": \"the North's reluctance\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1029}, {\"ngram\": \"a positive light\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"the blackout\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1086}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kim Jong Un himself used his annual televised New Year's address to wish for the games' success and announce the North's plan to participate, prompting officials from both Koreas to make a major effort so that Pyongyang could send more than 500 people, including 22 athletes and 21 reporters (none of whose work has been seen).\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1109, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jong-un\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kim Jong Un\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jong-un\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jong-un\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyongyang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4806370843782535e-24, \"text\": \"Pyongyang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyongyang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyongyang\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his annual televised New Year's address\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1173}, {\"ngram\": \"the games' success\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"the North's plan\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"both Koreas\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1287}, {\"ngram\": \"a major effort\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 500 people\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"22 athletes\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1383}, {\"ngram\": \"21 reporters\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1406}, {\"ngram\": \"whose work\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The North's gambit largely worked.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The North's gambit\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its all-female cheering squad and the singing performances piqued the interest of Olympic fans worldwide, though the athletes, mostly young and inexperienced in international events, won no medals and struggled just to keep up.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its all-female cheering squad\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"the singing performances\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"the interest\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic fans\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1567}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"international events\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"no medals\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"North Korean athletes are competing on the world stage, even if they are not winning,\\\" said Martyn Williams, a North Korea media watcher and creator of the North Korea Tech website.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1709, \"end\": 1715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.8535731816194198, \"rank\": 0.17154570338856012, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1795, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martyn_Williams\", \"score\": 0.9999994002861947, \"rank\": 5.997140538236194e-07, \"text\": \"Martyn Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martyn_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martyn_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.970882592400798e-17, \"text\": \"North Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 1859, \"end\": 1875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea_Tech\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"North Korea Tech\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea_Tech\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea_Tech\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world stage\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"creator\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1851}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So the lack of a mention is mystifying.\\\"\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the lack\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"a mention\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1910}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams said North Korea broadcast coverage of every Olympics going back to the 2004 Athens Summer Games, missing only the Vancouver Winter Olympics in 2010.\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1942, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.970882592400798e-17, \"text\": \"North Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vancouver Winter Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Winter_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Williams\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"coverage\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"every Olympics\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1990}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2004 Athens Summer Games\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said there may have been more, but that's as far as he is able to confirm.\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Previous Olympics generally got occasional reports, with a focus on the achievements of North Korean athletes, one or two days after the actual competition.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2260, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.8535731816194198, \"rank\": 0.17154570338856012, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Previous Olympics\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"occasional reports\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2216}, {\"ngram\": \"a focus\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"the achievements\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual competition\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time around, Williams said he has yet to see a \\\"single second\\\" of Olympics coverage on KCTV, the primary broadcaster.\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_Central_Television\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.894414031273309e-24, \"text\": \"KCTV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_Central_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_Central_Television\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Williams\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2350}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"single second\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2390}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics coverage\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2412}, {\"ngram\": \"the primary broadcaster\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Last weekend's 'International Sports News' program featured a cycle race from Dubai, European basketball and European football, but no Olympics,\\\" he noted.\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2527, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dubai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.880520728201293e-14, \"text\": \"Dubai\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dubai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dubai\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Last weekend's 'International Sports News' program\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2499}, {\"ngram\": \"a cycle race\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"European basketball\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"European football\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the evening news each evening, the Olympics have not been mentioned except in the context of the North Korean party delegation attending events.\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2712, \"end\": 2718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.8535731816194198, \"rank\": 0.17154570338856012, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the evening news\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2625}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2652}, {\"ngram\": \"the context\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2698}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2746, \"to\": 2752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even then, no video has been broadcast.\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2793, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no video\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 2773}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been covered with still images.\\\"\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"still images\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2829}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The absence of video might suggest a rights' issue - which is a legalistic can of worms.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The absence\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2844}, {\"ngram\": \"video\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2853}, {\"ngram\": \"a rights' issue\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2883}, {\"ngram\": \"a legalistic can\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2911}, {\"ngram\": \"worms\", \"from\": 2915, \"to\": 2920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two people involved with Olympic broadcast rights for the SBS network, initially the official rights holder for the whole peninsula, said their network returned rights for the North to broadcast the games directly to the International Olympic Committee but were not sure if Pyongyang had requested permission to use them.\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 3244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3144, \"end\": 3175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3197, \"end\": 3206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyongyang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4806370843782535e-24, \"text\": \"Pyongyang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyongyang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyongyang\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Two people\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic broadcast rights\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"the SBS network\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2992}, {\"ngram\": \"initially the official rights holder\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole peninsula\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3054}, {\"ngram\": \"their network\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3074}, {\"ngram\": \"rights\", \"from\": 3084, \"to\": 3090}, {\"ngram\": \"the North\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3104}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 3118, \"to\": 3127}, {\"ngram\": \"permission\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, the North would have gone through the non-profit Asia-Pacific Broadcasting Union, but concerns over possible sanctions violations might have made the IOC route more feasible.\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3332, \"end\": 3337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.258774637418489e-14, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3407, \"end\": 3410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.657579374077511e-30, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the North\", \"from\": 3257, \"to\": 3266}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3351}, {\"ngram\": \"possible sanctions violations\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3386}]}, {\"sentence\"